description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a new role in the Ambulatory Care Division to provide senior medical leadership for Clinical Governance. The Ambulatory Care Division wishes to appoint a Clinical Director for Clinical Governance to lead for the Division on clinical Quality and Safety issues.You would assist the Divisional Director and work in collaboration with the Divisional Lead Nurse for Clinical Governance. You would assume responsibility on behalf of the Divisional Director for overseeing specific elements of Clinical Governance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts will attract 2 PA’s and will form part of an individual’s substantive grade.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A copy of the Trust’s generic job description and person specification for this role are attached for information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like any more information or an informal chat please contact Dr Jo Lamb, Divisional Director via email Jo.Lamb@nuh.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
